# Heartbeat — Miles

## IMPORTANT: Heartbeat is DISABLED until Telegram is configured
<!-- OpenClaw heartbeats fire automatically and consume API credits silently.
     Do NOT enable until the Telegram channel is working and verified.
     Lesson learned from Open_Claw_v0: heartbeat ran up costs with no notification delivery. -->

## Schedule

### Daily (7:30 AM ET) — V1 Observation Cycle
This is Miles's primary activity. One cycle per day, using Haiku.

**Step 1 — Read Vault Snapshot:**
- Check `0. Dashboard/Daily Snapshots/` for today's snapshot (produced by Cowork daily-scan at 7:00 AM)
- Extract notable changes: Apollo pipeline state, Instantly inbound replies, git activity, file changes, Todoist completions, staleness warnings
- If no snapshot exists yet (Cowork hasn't run), proceed with API data only

**Step 2 — Call Apollo API:**
- Get active opportunities with contacts, stages, amounts, last touch dates
- Compare against yesterday's memory entries for movement detection
- Note: new deals, stage changes, stale deals (no activity >7 days)

**Step 3 — Call Todoist API:**
- Get open tasks with deadlines, priorities, project assignments
- Get recent completions (activity log)
- Note: overdue tasks, completed tasks, project activity patterns

**Step 4 — Read Work Calendar:**
- Get today's events from `andrew@wastenaut.ai` via GoG CLI
- Note: meeting count, total meeting hours, focus time availability
- If meetings involve known prospects (cross-reference Apollo), note for V2 pre-meeting briefs

**Step 5 — Read Family Calendar (Opaque):**
- Get today's time blocks from `drew.joiner@gmail.com` via GoG CLI
- Report ONLY as "Personal Conflict [start-end]" — never titles or details
- Purpose: understand total time availability (work + personal blocks)

**Step 6 — Compare and Write:**
- Compare today's observations against yesterday's MEMORY.md entries
- Write new observations to MEMORY.md with today's date
- Focus on deltas — what changed, not what stayed the same
- Format: one observation per line, date-stamped

### No Routine Heartbeat
- Unlike Ava (30-min system health check), Miles does NOT run a frequent heartbeat in V1
- One daily observation cycle is sufficient for the shadow period
- This minimizes API costs and avoids unnecessary processing
- V2+ may add more frequent checks if warranted

### Nightly (2:00 AM ET) — System Health
- Check container status, disk usage, memory usage
- Verify .env permissions are still 600
- Verify vault sync is running (check git log for recent commits)
- Do NOT send any messages — log only
- If critical issue detected (disk >90%, container down), log prominently for next morning review

## Notification Routing (V1)

| Priority | Channel | Timing |
|----------|---------|--------|
| Critical | N/A in V1 | Miles does not send unsolicited messages |
| On-demand | Telegram DM | When Andrew asks a question |
| Observation | MEMORY.md | After daily cycle |
| System health | Daily log | Nightly check |

